post_text:
Below is the letter from Superintendent Paul Clark about the learning options available to Cheboygan Area Schools families as school reopens in September. A copy will be mailed to each family as well. Please extend your patience and grace to Mr. Clark, the administrators, teachers and staff as they finalize plans to educate our children while also keeping over 1600 students and 300 staff members healthy all with a shrinking school budget. I am happy to compile questions for the administration but specific questions that need a quick answer are best addressed to Mr. Clark or the building principals. Their contact information is below. This is a challenging time for all involved, including Cheboygan families, and negative comments will be deleted. -Jenny Hayden

Mr. Clark-Superintendent clarkp@chebschools.com

Mrs. Duffton- East principal dufftond@chebschools.com

Mr. Duvall- CIS principal duvallm@chebschools.com

Mrs. Ackerman- CMS principal ackermanm@chebschools.com

Mrs. Spray- high school principal sprayn@chebschools.com,

post_text: Help wanted....Cheboygan Area Schools is looking for people who are willing to make or donate masks for in-person learning students to use once school starts. The masks should have ear loops and be at least 7.5"x5" for younger students and up to 10"x6" for older students. Completed masks can be dropped off at any school building or the Board of Education office. Any negative comments about masks will be deleted.

shared_text:
Cheboygan Opera House
April 21 at 9:59 AM 路

The Cheboygan Area Arts Council, home of the Cheboygan Opera House, will host the very first Virtual Youth Art Show, sponsored by Reusch Jewelers.

All grades and mediums welcome! To enter, send a photo of your artwork (3 submissions maximum per student) to Sean McNeil at mcneils@chebschools.com. Please include your full name, grade, and written permission from a parent allowing us to publish your artwork online. This art show will not be judged.

The Virtual Youth Art Show will start on May 1st. Keep an eye on the Cheboygan Opera House Facebook page and website for the virtual gallery!

3. What president is on this coin?

post_text: On Thursday, March 12th, CIS PAC group will be hosting a Warrior Ball Tournament for grades 3-5 in the CIS gym. Permission slips are being sent home and extras are in the office if your child would like to play. The cost is $3 to play and $2 to watch the game. Students who wish to play, MUST RETURN the permission slips with money by Thursday, March 5 at 11am . NO LATE ENTRIES will be accepted after March 5. 3rd graders will begin playing at 3:15 with 4th and 5th graders following. Family members are welcome to attend to watch and may pay the $2 entrance fee at the door. Concessions will be available for purchase and parking is available in the CIS,CMS,or High School parking lots and the bus lane will be open after 4pm. Come join the fun! Afterwards, please pick up your child in the cafeteria by 4:45.
